# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok the head of the council of labor affairs -lrb- cla -rrb- on friday expressed the hope that the labor standard law will be amended to lower wages for foreign workers .
# ::alignments
(e / express-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :ARG0-of (h / head-01
                  :ARG1 (o / organization
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "Council"
                              :op2 "of"
                              :op3 "Labor"
                              :op4 "Affairs"))))
      :ARG1 (h2 / hopeful-03
            :ARG0 p
            :ARG1 (a / amend-01
                  :ARG1 (l / law
                        :mod (s / standard
                              :mod (l2 / labor)))
                  :ARG2 (l3 / lower-05
                        :ARG0 l
                        :ARG1 (w / wage
                              :beneficiary (p2 / person
                                    :ARG0-of (w2 / work-01)
                                    :mod (f / foreign))))))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (f2 / friday)))

# ::id 1934 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

                        :mod (l / last)))

                  :quant 1000000000
                  :unit (f / franc
                        :mod (c / country

                                    :op1 "Switzerland")))
                  :ARG1-of (m2 / mean-01
                        :ARG2 (m3 / monetary-quantity
                              :quant 1000000000
                              :unit (e / euro)))))
      :time (w / wednesday)
      :ARG1-of (c2 / cause-01
            :ARG0 (h / hit-02
                  :ARG0 (a2 / and
                        :op1 (r2 / rule
                              :topic (a3 / account-01)
                              :ARG1-of (c3 / change-01))
                        :op2 (l2 / ligate-01)
                        :location c
                        :name (n4 / name
                              :op1 "United"
                              :op2 "States")))
            :ARG1 (f2 / figure
                  :poss g)))

                  :quant 1000000
